---
import IndustrialCta from "@/components/industrial/IndustrialCta.astro";
import SectionBlock from "@/components/industrial/SectionBlock.astro";
import SplitPageLayout from "@/components/industrial/SplitPageLayout.astro";
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "Why Sikhs Must Be Prepared - Understanding Our Sacred Duty",
	title: "Why - Sacred Duty",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<SplitPageLayout
		sectionNumber="02"
		sectionLabel="Systems"
		title="Modern Weapons, Modern Responsibilities"
		subtitle="Contemporary platforms. Ancestral discipline. Unchanged principles."
	>
		<SectionBlock number="01" visualSrc="/assets/images/industrial/hero-rifle.jpg" visualAlt="Modern tactical platform">
			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				Just as our ancestors maintained the most effective weapons of their time, today's Sikhs have a duty to be
				properly equipped with modern defensive tools. Modern rifles and handguns should be respected and understood,
				not feared. They are extensions of our tradition of preparedness and protection.
			</p>

			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				History has shown that evil does not rest, and the only way to prevent suffering at the hands of tyrants is to
				maintain the highest level of defensive capability legally permitted. This includes modern sporting rifles and
				similar platforms - if those who wish harm can access such tools, it is our duty to be equally prepared to
				defend the innocent.
			</p>

			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				Remember that Guru Gobind Singh Ji equipped the Khalsa with the most advanced arms available in their time.
				Today, we honor that tradition by maintaining proficiency with modern defensive tools while upholding the same
				principles of restraint, discipline, and righteousness.
			</p>
		</SectionBlock>

		<SectionBlock number="02">
			<div class="icomat-zoom-wrap group relative mx-auto mb-8 max-w-[600px] overflow-hidden border border-black/15 dark:border-white/10">
				<img
					src="/assets/images/Shaastar.png"
					alt="Traditional Sikh Martial Arts"
					class="icomat-zoom-target mx-auto block w-full p-4"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Embracing Modern Arms</h2>
			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				Modern firearms, including rifles and handguns, should be viewed as tools of liberation and protection, not
				instruments of fear. They represent our continued commitment to defending dharma in an evolving world. Just as
				our ancestors mastered the weapons of their time, we must embrace and understand contemporary defensive tools.
			</p>
		</SectionBlock>

		<SectionBlock number="03" visualSrc="/assets/images/industrial/section-optics.jpg" visualAlt="Precision optics and engineering">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Defending Our Rights</h2>
			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				In the United States, the Second Amendment enshrines the fundamental right to bear arms - a right that
				aligns perfectly with Sikh principles of self-defense and community protection. We must actively support and
				defend this constitutional right, understanding that an armed and trained citizenry is the best safeguard
				against tyranny and oppression.
			</p>

			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				For Sikhs worldwide, we must advocate for similar liberties in other nations. The right to armed self-defense
				is not just an American principle - it is a human right that the Khalsa has defended for centuries. Whether in
				India, Canada, or Europe, Sikhs should work within legal frameworks to preserve and expand the rights of
				responsible citizens to own and train with defensive weapons.
			</p>
		</SectionBlock>

		<SectionBlock number="04" visualSrc="/assets/images/industrial/section-precision.jpg" visualAlt="Industrial manufacturing precision">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Maximum Preparedness</h2>
			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				History has repeatedly shown that evil persists, and the only effective deterrent is maintaining the highest
				level of defensive capability within legal bounds. This includes modern sporting rifles and similar platforms
				- when those who intend harm have access to such tools, we have a sacred duty to be equally prepared to
				protect the innocent.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg mb-4">
				Our tradition demands we remain properly equipped and trained with the most effective defensive tools available.
				This preparedness serves as both deterrent and protection, upholding our historical responsibility as guardians
				of righteousness.
			</p>

			<blockquote class="icomat-quote my-8">
				"ਸਵਾ ਲਾਖ ਸੇ ਏਕ ਲੜਾਊਂ"
				<br />
				<span class="text-sm mt-2 block">
					"I will make one fight against 125,000" - Guru Gobind Singh Ji
				</span>
			</blockquote>

			<IndustrialCta href="/contact" label="Connect" />
		</SectionBlock>
	</SplitPageLayout>
</PageLayout>
